In the anguished groves of mankind's soul,
Where sorrow dwells in every heart,
The chains of ignorance are slowly breaking,
And tyranny begins to fall apart.
For we have learned that all men are created equal,
That all share in one precious gift -
The right to life and liberty,
As well as the pursuit of happiness.

Raised in hatred and intolerance,
Preaching division and discord,
And sowing seeds of bitterness.

In even the darkest corners of the earth,
As those who suffer from injustice,

The barriers that have kept us apart for so long,
And bring about a brighter world to come.

So let us join hands and hearts today,
In solidarity and unity,
To fight for justice and equality,
For peace and brotherhood in harmony with thee.
Let every nation turn from hatred's path,
And choose instead the way of love,
That all people may live together free,
In a world where social issues no longer prove.
